title: National Register of Historic Places listings in Meeker County, Minnesota
data: Farmhouse built 1888-89 by prosperous local brickmaker Henry Ames ( 1846-1928 ) , whose on-site brickyard was Meeker County 's leading industry for almost two decades
690th Avenue over the North Fork of the Crow River 45°12′08″N 94°22′45″W / 45.202092°N 94.37917°W / 45.202092 ; -94.37917 ( Bridge No . 90980 )
One of Minnesota 's earliest steel truss bridges , built in 1899 by the Hewett Bridge Company , an important Minneapolis-based manufacturer at the turn of the 20th century
South Ripley Drive 45°05′54″N 94°32′22″W / 45.098285°N 94.539338°W / 45.098285 ; -94.539338 ( Brightwood Beach Cottage )

Octagonal summer cottage built for a lake resort in 1889 , Minnesota 's only surviving example of the octagon house fad applied to a rental property and the best representative of the short-lived resort 's facilities
One-room school active 1870-1961 , a remnant of early Euro-American settlement and education in rural Minnesota
Grand Army of the Republic Hall
370 North Marshall Street 45°07′45″N 94°31′35″W / 45.129137°N 94.526322°W / 45.129137 ; -94.526322 ( Grand Army of the Republic Hall )

Fortress-like hall built in 1885 by Civil War Union Veterans to house a private reading library and museum ; one of the finest buildings associated with influential late 19th-century fraternal society Grand Army of the Republic . Now part of the Meeker County Historical Society Museum
North Sibley Avenue between Depot and Third Streets 45°07′39″N 94°31′41″W / 45.127404°N 94.528111°W / 45.127404 ; -94.528111 ( Litchfield Commercial Historic District )
Unusually intact business district of a small Midwestern agricultural trade center of the late 19th and early 20th centuries , with 36 contributing properties mostly built between 1882 and 1940
Long-serving community center , built as a theater in 1900 and remodeled in the 1930s to house civic offices and public meeting space
Best preserved example of 12 sod forts built and briefly manned by the U.S. Army across southwest Minnesota in the year after the Dakota War of 1862
Superlative Carpenter Gothic church built in 1871 , believed to have been designed by Richard Upjohn
901 First Street , North 45°05′10″N 94°18′28″W / 45.086195°N 94.30779°W / 45.086195 ; -94.30779 ( Universal Laboratories Building )

Processing facility that became the nation 's first and most important domestic supplier of ergot - source of many vital drugs , particularly in wartime - beginning in 1937 just as the impending World War II was cutting off foreign purveyors . Now a museum
